        <h2>Shouldn't there be more stylised ligatures?</h2>
        <p>
            There are quite a few ligatures I left out, like <code>LA</code>, or the <code>A</code> or <code>N</code> being "truncated" by neighbouring characters. While I could create a large set of lignatures like that, it would end up being a lot of work that I just don't have time for right now. If you're using vector programs, you can use tools like Adobe Illustrator's Pathfinder to cut out part of a letter with another one to get that result.
        </p>
    </div>
